## 1. Project Overview

**hmpsn.studio** is an SEO/web analytics platform built with **React 19 + Vite 8 + TailwindCSS 4 + React Router DOM 7** (frontend) and **Express + TypeScript** (backend). It manages client websites via Webflow, Google Search Console, GA4, and SEMRush integrations.

- **Routing** — **React Router DOM 7** (`src/routes.ts` defines `Page` + `ClientTab` types, `adminPath()` + `clientPath()` helpers). Admin: `/ws/:workspaceId/:tab?`, Client: `/client/:workspaceId/:tab?`, global tabs: `/settings`, `/roadmap`, `/prospect`, `/ai-usage`.
- **API Client** — Typed fetch wrappers in `src/api/` (9 modules). All components import from `src/api/` — no raw `fetch()` calls in components. `ApiError` class with `.status` for error handling.
- **Shared Types** — `shared/types/` (10 modules) shared between client and server. Canonical interfaces for workspace, analytics, content, payments, approvals, etc.
- **Storage** — **SQLite** via `better-sqlite3` (WAL mode, foreign keys ON) at `DATA_BASE/dashboard.db`. All 5 migration PRs merged to `main` — 30+ modules now use SQLite. See § 2a below.
- **AI** — OpenAI GPT-4.1/4.1-mini/4.1-nano via `server/openai-helpers.ts` (`callOpenAI`), Anthropic Claude via `server/anthropic-helpers.ts` (`callAnthropic`) for creative prose
- **Payments** — Stripe Checkout (not Payment Intents). Config encrypted on disk (AES-256-GCM). Admin UI for keys + products.
- **Auth** — Dual system: internal JWT (7-day, admin) + client JWT (24h, per-workspace). Legacy shared-password still supported. Turnstile CAPTCHA on client login/forgot-password (optional).
- **Monetization** — 3 tiers (Free/Growth/Premium), per-item content purchases, 14-day Growth trial, UX soft-gating via `<TierGate>`
- **Logging** — **Pino** structured JSON logging (`server/logger.ts`). `createLogger(module)` for child loggers. Pretty-print in dev, JSON in prod.
- **Error monitoring** — **Sentry** (`server/sentry.ts` + frontend `@sentry/react`). Auto-tags errors with `workspaceId`. Conditional source maps.
- **CI/CD** — GitHub Actions (`.github/workflows/ci.yml` for lint/test/build, `e2e.yml` for Playwright).
- **Graceful shutdown** — SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers: flush email queue, close DB, close WebSocket, clean exit.
- **Backups** — Local periodic backups + optional S3 off-site upload (`BACKUP_S3_BUCKET`).

